FBIS3-34341 "drnes025_n_94002" FBIS-NES-94-025 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Feb 1994 LEBANON Roundup of 4-7 Feb Clashes in Southern Region Three SLA Soldiers Wounded NC0502083194 Kafr Killa Voice of the South in Arabic 0800 GMT 5 Feb 94 NC0502083194 Kafr Killa Voice of the South Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Three South Lebanese Army [SLA] soldiers were slightly injured when a mine exploded on the road between the villages of Markaba and Tallusah yesterday afternoon. Another SLA force detonated a land mine which it had discovered in the Jazzin area yesterday morning. The SLA force suffered no casualties. In the Western sector, an Israeli Army patrol came under terrorist fire. The patrol returned the fire. The patrol suffered no casualties.
